On the 60th anniversary of the March on Washington, a shooting occurred in Jacksonville, taking the lives of three Black Americans. Law enforcement is investigating the attack as a possible hate crime and act of domestic violent extremism. The article emphasizes that America is currently facing an epidemic of hate, with many communities torn apart by hatred and violent extremism. The fear of being victims of hate-fueled gun violence is a daily reality for many Black Americans. The article calls for Congress to ban assault weapons and pass gun safety legislation to ensure the freedom to live safe from gun violence. The author offers prayers for the victims and their loved ones.